-- Colombian Stock Movers: Corficolombiana, Ecopetrol, Proenergia
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-16T21:50:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/colombian-stock-movers-corficolombiana-ecopetrol-proenergia.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  dropped 0.3 percent to 13,080.71, while the
Colcap Index declined 0.9 percent to 1,578.22.  Corp. Financiera Colombiana SA (CORFICOL CB), the
financial-services and holding company with investments in the
construction industry, fell 0.6 percent to 34,100 pesos. The
company said it plans to sell 13.3 million shares of  Proenergia
Internacional SA (PROENERG)  to Grand Cayman-based Copec Investments Ltd.,
according to a regulatory filing Jan. 13. The sale price per
share was set at 9,280 pesos, the filing said.  Proenergia Internacional SA (PROENERG CB), a Colombian
wholesaler and retailer of compressed natural gas, rose 3.1
percent to 8,760 pesos.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil producer,
fell 1.5 percent to 4,415 pesos after the company said protests
are reducing supplies from a field in northern  Colombia .  Protesters blockading roadways and hampering the entry of
workers have reduced output at the Ciras Infantas field since
this weekend, according to a company official who can’t be
identified because of corporate policy. The field usually
produces 28,000 to 30,000 barrels a day of crude, the official
said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
